            <fr:title text="Mutual information is nonnegative">Mutual information is nonnegative</fr:title>
            <fr:taxon>Theorem</fr:taxon>
          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter>
            <html:p>For any pair of random variables, <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[I(X;Y)\geq  0]]></fr:tex>, with equality iff <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[X]]></fr:tex> and <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[Y]]></fr:tex> are independent.</html:p>
            <html:p>This is <fr:link href="/004E/" title="Gibb's inequality" uri="https://kellenkanarios.com/004E/" display-uri="004E" type="local">Gibb's inequality</fr:link> in disguise: <fr:link href="/000V/" title="Mutual Information" uri="https://kellenkanarios.com/000V/" display-uri="000V" type="local">mutual information</fr:link> is the <fr:link href="/000W/" title="Kullback-Liebler Divergence" uri="https://kellenkanarios.com/000W/" display-uri="000W" type="local">KL divergence</fr:link> between the joint distribution and the product of marginals,
<fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[I(X;Y)\ =\ D_{\mathrm {KL}}\left (P_{XY}\,\|\,P_X P_Y\right )\ \geq \ 0,]]></fr:tex>
and Gibbs' inequality forces every KL divergence to be nonnegative, vanishing exactly when the two arguments coincide — i.e. when <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[P_{XY}=P_XP_Y]]></fr:tex>. It is the root fact from which <fr:link href="/H7J5/" title="Conditioning reduces entropy" uri="https://kellenkanarios.com/H7J5/" display-uri="H7J5" type="local">Conditioning reduces entropy</fr:link> follows.</html:p>
          </fr:mainmatter>
        </fr:tree>
